s-now-one-of-us!Tabletopgamingnews.com Tabletopgamingnews.com Acquisition announcement retrieved May 3rd 2013]</ref> and currently operates it.\n\n===Ravage USA===\nCoolMiniOrNot publishes the English language edition of Ravage magazine.\n\n===Crystal Brush painting competition===\nThe company also organizes an annual [[miniature figure painting]] competition with a cash purse of $10,000, $2,000 and $1,000 for the overall winners. The competition has guest judges which account for 50% of the total score, with a 12 hour Internet vote making up the remaining 50%.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|www.cmon.com}}\n* [http://www.tabletopgamingnews.com Tabletopgamingnews.com]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20130507130200/http://ravageusa.com/ Ravage USA]\n* [http://www.crystalbrush.com Crystal Brush official site]\n* [https://kick.agency/news KA | Board Game News]\n\n[[Category:Companies based in Fulton County, Georgia]]\n[[Category:Gaming miniatures companies]]\n[[Category:Board game publishing companies]]\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2001]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name             = CMON Limited\n| type             = [[Public Corporation]]\n| industry         = [[Miniature wargaming]] and [[Board game]] publisher\n| subsid           = CMON Inc\n| foundation       = 2001\n| hq_location_country = Singapore\n| key_people       = Chern Ann Ng (CEO), David Doust (co-founder)\n| products         = \n| homepage         = {{URL|www.cmon.com}}\n| footnotes        = \n| revenue = US$17 million <ref>{{cite web |url=http://gem.ednews.hk/listedco/listconews/GEM/2016/1125/GLN20161125003.pdf |title=CMON Limited Prospectus |author=CMON Limited |date=December 2, 2016 |publisher=Hong Kong Stock Exchange }}</ref>\n| revenue_year = 2015\n| logo = File:Logo_CMON.png\n| traded_as = {{SEHK|1792}}\n}}\n'''CMON Limited''', formerly known as '''CoolMiniOrNot''' is a publicly listed miniatures and board game publisher, trading on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange. It also operates a miniatures related site coolminiornot.com <ref>[http://www.similarweb.com/website/coolminiornot.com 6th in the world in the Gaming/Miniatures category according to Similarweb as of May 3rd, 2013]</ref> that features user submitted images of their painted models for voting.\n\n==History==\nCoolMiniOrNot was founded as a community site for posting images of painted miniatures, inspired by [[Hot or Not]] style dating sites.<ref>[http://www.wampforum.com/content.php?r=260-Interview-with-Chern-Ann Interview WAMP interview with Chern Ann Ng, retrieved May 3rd, 2013]</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20010720071441/http://www.coolminiornot.com/ Wayback Machine Archive of coolminiornot.com July 20th, 2001 retrieved May 3rd, 2013]</ref>\n\nIt later began publishing board games and miniature games, notable titles include [[Super Dungeon Explore]]<ref>[http://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/92190/super-dungeon-explore Boardgamegeek Super Dungeon Explore listing]</ref> in 2011 and [[Zombicide]]<ref>[http://boardgamegeek.com/boardgame/113924/zombicide Boardgamegeek Zombicide listing]</ref> in 2012.\n\nSome of its games are critically acclaimed, with three games (Xenoshyft, Rum and Bones and Blood Rage) making [[The Dice Tower]]'s top 10 games of 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a3FB_oqfo1o |title=Top 10 Games of 2015 |author=The Dice Tower |date=December 15, 2015 |publisher=YouTube }}</ref>\n\nOn December 2, 2016, CMON Limited began publicly trading on the GEM board of the Hong Kong Stock Exchange.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hkex.com.hk/eng/market/partcir/hkscc/2016/Documents/ce301_2016.pdf |title=Stock Admission - New Listing of Securities |author=CMON Limited |date=December 2, 2016 |publisher=Hong Kong Securities Clearing Company Limited }}</ref>\n\nTrading of CMON Ltd was halted on April 1, 2020 after having audit issues.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://icv2.com/articles/news/view/45581/annual-report-delayed-trading-suspended-cmon?fbclid=IwAR1SquWmVuleOhkP4lWL4p3zkaCEXsrXvQNrvRqFetZ93-IG4TgyafmFpxE |title=Annual Report Delayed, Trading Suspended in CMON |author=Milton Griepp |date=April 10, 2020 |publisher=icv2 }}</ref>\n\n==Kickstarter activity==\nCoolMiniOrNot has used [[Kickstarter]] with relative success occupying several places in the Most Funded Tabletop Games category.<ref>[https://www.kickstarter.com/discover/advanced?state=successful&category_id=34&sort=most_funded Kickstarter Tabletop Games / Most Funded retrieved June 13, 2015]</ref>  The total amount raised thus far is $38,112,581, and the company actively pursues a strategy of Kickstarter to create new products.<ref>[http://www.icv2.com/articles/news/25446.html ICV2 interview with David Doust]</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ CoolMiniOrNot's Kickstarter projects<ref>[http://www.kickstarter.com/profile/cmon/created Kickstarter project list for CMON Retrieved June 13th, 2017]</ref>\n|-\n! Total USD !! Project name !! % funded !! Backers !! Closing date \n|-\n\n| style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:8px;\"| 4,013,731|| Bloodborne: The Board Game|| style=\"text-align:right;\" |2,007||style=\"text-align:right;\" |23,986||style=\"text-align:center;\"|2019-05-14\n|-\n\n| style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:8px;\"| 634,782 || Project: Elite || style=\"text-align:right;\" |635 ||style=\"text-align:right;\" |5,367 ||style=\"text-align:center;\"|2018-11-12\n|-\n\n| style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:8px;\"| 935,956 || Starcadia Quest || style=\"text-align:right;\" | 468 ||style=\"text-align:right;\" |6,503 ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2018-09-11\n|-\n\n| style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:8px;\"| 2,412,286 || Cthulhu: Death May Die ||style=\"text-align:right;\" | 1,206 ||style=\"text-align:right;\" |15,831 ||style=\"text-align:center;\"| 2018-07-24\n|-\n\n| style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:8px;\"| 316,018 || Arcadia Quest: Riders ||style=\"text-align:right;\" | 1,0